comments.body:
It looks mostly good to me. The only comment I have is that the code should no longer support unlimited number of children in a directory, which is in {{FSDirectory#verifyMaxDirItems()}}.

{code}
    if (maxDirItems == 0) {
      return;
    }
{code}

Otherwise users might run into a problem that the saved fsimage cannot be consumed. Do you think it is a good idea to enforce a maximum limit, say, 6.7m based on your calculation?
